    },
    {
      "id": "16104cb686646b43ba4553688d51f8c249bc7c21",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2021-03-30 11:52:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> > Amir, it took me some time to get access but I got some data,\n > I've\n > > updated the ticket.\n > \n > I don't see this information in the ticket. Can you make it public?\n\nChris, the comment has some sen\n\n > > Amir, it took me some time to get access but I got some data,\n > I've\n > > updated the ticket.\n > \n > I don't see this information in the ticket. Can you make it public?\n\nChris, the comment is now public in the ticket.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c09dfdfdfec70e127f9b3c7faf434460c7a9ec20",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 824,
        "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
        "email": "ssmirnov@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "ssmirnov"
      },
      "date": "2021-04-03 18:56:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "402521bdcb6b083e50a51f0d09ee40662f49d12c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2021-04-04 01:08:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt looks from the comment that with 42111 the mount improves by 6 seconds? Is my understanding correct? I didn't get the 30 minute comment. Was the 30 minute mount time without 42109?\nMy concern with this change is that in some conditions, when the nodes are coming up simultaneously there will be 0 retries on connections which otherwise would've succeeded. Say in the case when the a node is just coming up and you try to connect, but the listener isn't there yet.\nThis patch prevents retries completely. While there currently exists a tunable to set the retry count to 0 (or less than 5)\nNow I understand this is a narrow race condition, but I'm unsure of the impact of this patch generally. Would it make sense for the affected site to simply set the number of retries to 0?\nI'll +1 this for now, but I'm unsure if it'll cause other problems.\nChris, what's your take on this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "699246827dffcf34491c6c733615b88a42997c09",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2021-04-06 00:16:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It looks from the comment that with 42111 the mount improves by 6\n > seconds? Is my understanding correct? I didn't get the 30 minute\n > comment. Was the 30 minute mount time without 42109?\n > My concern with this change is that in some conditions, when the\n > nodes are coming up simultaneously there will be 0 retries on\n > connections which otherwise would've succeeded. Say in the case\n > when the a node is just coming up and you try to connect, but the\n > listener isn't there yet.\n > This patch prevents retries completely. While there currently\n > exists a tunable to set the retry count to 0 (or less than 5)\n > Now I understand this is a narrow race condition, but I'm unsure of\n > the impact of this patch generally. Would it make sense for the\n > affected site to simply set the number of retries to 0?\n > I'll +1 this for now, but I'm unsure if it'll cause other problems.\n > Chris, what's your take on this?\n\nAmir, the mount time is 30 min with latest 2.12\nand 15 sec with 42109, 8 sec with both 42109 and 42111.\nso yes, 42111 improves mount time by 6 seconds for that site.\n\nThis patch is more like an RFC, as I'm not sure about the complications after not retrying. The reason I pushed this patch\nis currently ksocklnd is not retrying if there's no listener(correct me if I'm wrong).\n\nIf we are in doubt, we can land 42109 only, it cuts down mount time from 30 mins to 15 sec, another 6 sec on top of that is great but not essential.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bbd34456ba8997a4065aaf28db7de7cae5c5210a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2021-04-06 14:06:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Chris, what's your take on this?\n\nThe patch isn't needed to resolve the customer issue, and we have a tunable to do the same thing. I'd say this patch should not land unless a more compelling case can be made for it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
